1
00:00:17,801 --> 00:00:19,401
(Episode 14)

2
00:00:36,801 --> 00:00:38,001
In the next life,

3
00:00:39,701 --> 00:00:40,831
give her up.

4
00:00:53,207 --> 00:00:54,207
Hey, Yul.

5
00:00:54,747 --> 00:00:56,447
What are you doing here alone?

6
00:00:56,607 --> 00:00:58,247
Everyone wants you to join them.

7
00:01:02,107 --> 00:01:03,507
Come on. Let's go.

8
00:01:08,647 --> 00:01:09,747
Look. Over there.

9
00:01:22,177 --> 00:01:24,547
What if you were born again after Joseon got liberated?

10
00:01:24,807 --> 00:01:26,047
What would you like to be?

11
00:01:30,647 --> 00:01:33,977
If I were to be born again after Joseon gets liberated,

12
00:01:35,207 --> 00:01:36,207
then...

13
00:01:37,507 --> 00:01:38,577
Then...

14
00:01:39,877 --> 00:01:40,907
Then...

15
00:01:42,277 --> 00:01:43,407
Even then,

16
00:01:44,307 --> 00:01:46,877
I hope I will be beside you...

17
00:01:47,947 --> 00:01:49,007
and everyone else here.

18
00:02:12,047 --> 00:02:14,377
(Chicago Typewriter)

19
00:02:18,447 --> 00:02:20,747
Bang Jin, please close the curtains.

20
00:02:36,217 --> 00:02:38,677
Shall I start the morning of a successful mania?

21
00:02:42,377 --> 00:02:44,507
I said I'll do it by myself. You can go back inside.

22
00:02:45,007 --> 00:02:48,177
I get that you're trying to earn brownie points from Seol.

23
00:02:48,807 --> 00:02:51,607
Human beings can serve food for ghosts for ancestral rites,

24
00:02:51,607 --> 00:02:54,877
but no ghost has ever prepared breakfast for a human being.

25
00:02:55,347 --> 00:02:56,677
You're the one who should go inside.

26
00:02:57,807 --> 00:03:00,877
Don't underestimate me. The first place I arrived as a ghost...

27
00:03:01,107 --> 00:03:03,207
was a historic restaurant in Europe.

28
00:03:03,277 --> 00:03:05,207
I learned a lot by watching the chef cook.

29
00:03:05,207 --> 00:03:08,107
I guess that chef never shut his mouth while he cooked.

30
00:03:08,877 --> 00:03:12,307
I've collected a lot of data about cooking for a long period of time.

31
00:03:13,207 --> 00:03:14,877
My cooking skills are as good as a chef's.

32
00:03:15,207 --> 00:03:17,877
Then I guess we could let Seol choose today's menu for breakfast.

33
00:03:18,577 --> 00:03:19,777
What are you guys doing?

34
00:03:20,147 --> 00:03:21,477
Did you sleep well?

35
00:03:21,547 --> 00:03:22,877
You're awake.

36
00:03:23,547 --> 00:03:25,507
We're preparing breakfast.

37
00:03:26,607 --> 00:03:29,147
Did you guys always cook breakfast for yourselves?

38
00:03:29,577 --> 00:03:32,647
Of course, we didn't. I told the workers to take a few days off.

39
00:03:34,447 --> 00:03:36,177
Are you going to cook everything here for breakfast?

40
00:03:37,207 --> 00:03:40,477
Didn't you guys eat noodles with me last night?

41
00:03:40,547 --> 00:03:42,777
That's already been digested.

42
00:03:42,777 --> 00:03:44,177
Shouldn't you guys stay in shape?

43
00:03:44,177 --> 00:03:46,107
Men also take care of their figures these days.

44
00:03:46,107 --> 00:03:48,107
I heard that they do.

45
00:03:49,077 --> 00:03:52,447
But I was born with a great figure, so I never really felt the need to.

46
00:03:53,347 --> 00:03:55,207
You were doing pushups like crazy earlier.

47
00:03:55,207 --> 00:03:56,647
I think you did about 200 pushups.

48
00:04:02,047 --> 00:04:04,477
So what's for breakfast?

49
00:04:26,577 --> 00:04:28,547
Gyun Woo, here's your breakfast.

50
00:04:29,807 --> 00:04:31,547
I cooked this just for you.

51
00:04:32,077 --> 00:04:33,707
If you're reminded of something you have to do,

52
00:04:34,017 --> 00:04:35,207
do it now.

53
00:04:35,447 --> 00:04:37,447
Let's take a bath.

54
00:04:37,877 --> 00:04:39,347
That's a good boy.

55
00:04:43,077 --> 00:04:44,207
How cute.

56
00:04:44,647 --> 00:04:45,977
I'll do it.

57
00:04:46,277 --> 00:04:48,147
The sky may be clear today,

58
00:04:48,747 --> 00:04:50,977
but it might be cloudy tomorrow.

59
00:04:51,107 --> 00:04:52,477
Hurry up and get him.

60
00:04:52,907 --> 00:04:53,977
Gyun Woo.

61
00:04:54,347 --> 00:04:55,377
Hey!

62
00:04:59,177 --> 00:05:01,407
Yesterday is no longer yours.

63
00:05:01,907 --> 00:05:03,017
So do it now.

64
00:05:04,077 --> 00:05:05,107
Gyun Woo.

65
00:05:06,547 --> 00:05:08,477
Hey, Gyun Woo!

66
00:05:08,607 --> 00:05:10,107
Good boy.

67
00:05:15,047 --> 00:05:16,047
You look good.

68
00:05:18,207 --> 00:05:19,347
- Good boy. - Come here.

69
00:05:19,647 --> 00:05:20,647
You're so cute.

70
00:05:25,577 --> 00:05:26,647
Good boy.

71
00:05:31,607 --> 00:05:35,007
Good boy. You're so handsome. That's a good boy.

72
00:05:36,147 --> 00:05:37,347
My goodness.

73
00:05:39,077 --> 00:05:40,447
Good boy.

74
00:05:41,207 --> 00:05:42,607
That's a good boy.

75
00:05:42,907 --> 00:05:44,347
Good boy.

76
00:05:54,007 --> 00:05:56,207
If you wish to say something kind,

77
00:05:56,707 --> 00:05:58,007
say it now.

78
00:05:59,077 --> 00:06:02,407
- There might not be a tomorrow. - Come here.

79
00:06:05,507 --> 00:06:06,847
The person you love...

80
00:06:07,677 --> 00:06:09,807
won't always be next to you.

81
00:06:33,207 --> 00:06:34,777
If you wish to show affection,

82
00:06:35,277 --> 00:06:36,477
show it now.

83
00:06:37,777 --> 00:06:39,377
If you wish to smile,

84
00:06:39,707 --> 00:06:41,177
smile right now.

85
00:06:54,807 --> 00:06:55,847
Do it...

86
00:06:56,607 --> 00:06:57,607
right now.

87
00:07:01,047 --> 00:07:02,477
Do it...

88
00:07:03,477 --> 00:07:04,607
before your friend disappears.

89
00:07:34,647 --> 00:07:36,777
("Fate", First draft)

90
00:07:46,077 --> 00:07:48,377
(To Mr. Song at LK News, 17-3 Sangamro, Mapo-gu, Seoul)

91
00:07:51,547 --> 00:07:52,547
(To Mr. Song at LK News, 17-3 Sangamro, Mapo-gu, Seoul)

92
00:07:57,047 --> 00:07:59,207
("Fate", First draft)

93
00:08:01,407 --> 00:08:05,047
("Fate", First draft)

94
00:08:08,207 --> 00:08:10,977
("Fate", First draft, Written by Han Se Ju)

95
00:08:15,877 --> 00:08:18,807
(Han Se Ju, Yoo Jin Oh, Jeon Seol)

96
00:08:19,277 --> 00:08:20,277
Here.

97
00:08:22,747 --> 00:08:26,077
Okay. Now that we've signed the contract,

98
00:08:26,677 --> 00:08:29,207
shall we begin writing our novel?

99
00:08:30,577 --> 00:08:33,377
First, let's start with sharing your stories...

100
00:08:33,507 --> 00:08:35,477
of what you've experienced in your past life.

101
00:08:36,547 --> 00:08:39,707
I'm sure there was a secret agent in our organization.

102
00:08:40,117 --> 00:08:43,447
Shin Yul meeting Heo Young Min was all part of the plan,

103
00:08:43,807 --> 00:08:46,507
so that confirms that you weren't the secret agent.

104
00:08:48,077 --> 00:08:50,547
Then who in world was the secret agent?

105
00:08:57,207 --> 00:08:58,207
It could be...

106
00:08:58,977 --> 00:09:00,647
someone I know.

107
00:09:01,207 --> 00:09:02,277
Someone you know?

108
00:09:03,207 --> 00:09:04,347
Who could that be?

109
00:09:05,617 --> 00:09:07,207
My mom.

110
00:09:09,377 --> 00:09:10,577
What are you talking about?

111
00:09:11,377 --> 00:09:12,747
Why would your mom do that?

112
00:09:14,677 --> 00:09:18,477
To be honest, she recently came over and told me...

113
00:09:19,647 --> 00:09:22,347
that she also remembers her past life.

114
00:09:24,077 --> 00:09:26,207
She told me that I was part of that memory.

115
00:09:28,577 --> 00:09:30,947
And back when I experienced my past life,

116
00:09:32,007 --> 00:09:33,307
I saw my mom's face.

117
00:09:34,207 --> 00:09:35,507
Who was she?

118
00:09:41,207 --> 00:09:43,207
She was the manager of Carpe Diem.

119
00:09:44,277 --> 00:09:46,347
Madam Sophia?

120
00:09:59,117 --> 00:10:00,307
Why aren't you keeping your promise?

121
00:10:00,377 --> 00:10:03,207
You promised to get my son out of prison if I gave you information.

122
00:10:05,007 --> 00:10:07,007
He killed a Japanese policeman.

123
00:10:07,347 --> 00:10:09,177
Did you think you could save a murderer...

124
00:10:09,447 --> 00:10:11,747
with such useless information?

125
00:10:12,847 --> 00:10:15,807
All I know is the date and place of the mission.

126
00:10:16,707 --> 00:10:18,447
I need to know who the leader is.

127
00:10:18,777 --> 00:10:19,947
I told you that I don't know.

128
00:10:20,407 --> 00:10:21,777
I'm nothing but a manager.

129
00:10:22,047 --> 00:10:23,677
I've never even seen the leader's shadow.

130
00:10:23,747 --> 00:10:27,547
That's why I'm asking you to do your best and find out who he is.

131
00:10:29,307 --> 00:10:30,377
I can't keep doing this.

132
00:10:30,977 --> 00:10:33,047
If I continue, I'll get caught.

133
00:10:33,617 --> 00:10:35,277
If you get me the leader,

134
00:10:35,707 --> 00:10:37,907
not only will I get your son out of prison,

135
00:10:38,447 --> 00:10:40,647
but I'll also help you both escape to a safe place.

136
00:10:41,447 --> 00:10:43,617
From what I know, anyone who betrays the organization...

137
00:10:43,777 --> 00:10:45,747
will end up getting severely punished.

138
00:10:47,547 --> 00:10:48,547
There's also...

139
00:10:48,807 --> 00:10:51,707
one more thing I'd like you to do.

140
00:10:53,847 --> 00:10:55,477
Mom clearly said it.

141
00:10:56,007 --> 00:10:57,647
She said she left me because she was afraid...

142
00:10:57,647 --> 00:10:58,977
that the ill-fated relationship of the past life would repeat.

143
00:11:00,207 --> 00:11:03,977
I went to see her to find out about that ill-fated relationship.

144
00:11:04,777 --> 00:11:06,477
But she was already gone,

145
00:11:06,877 --> 00:11:08,147
and I couldn't meet her.

146
00:11:09,447 --> 00:11:10,607
How can this happen?

147
00:11:11,847 --> 00:11:13,507
I've been thinking since then.

148
00:11:14,647 --> 00:11:16,977
What was the ill-fated relationship she was referring to?

149
00:11:18,847 --> 00:11:21,577
What was the past life event that shouldn't be repeated?

150
00:11:23,377 --> 00:11:25,347
Then I remembered.

151
00:11:26,447 --> 00:11:27,447
Remember what?

152
00:11:29,277 --> 00:11:31,507
How the ill-fated relationship with Mom began.

153
00:11:35,947 --> 00:11:38,507
I was convinced that Mom was the secret agent.

154
00:11:39,907 --> 00:11:40,947
Also,

155
00:11:42,177 --> 00:11:45,377
I figured out how I got involved in that mission.

156
00:11:46,677 --> 00:11:48,177
Who did you say asked for me?

157
00:11:48,577 --> 00:11:50,747
Heo Young Min. He's the son of Mr. Nam, the writer.

158
00:11:52,277 --> 00:11:53,877
Why would he ask for me?

159
00:11:53,947 --> 00:11:55,207
Am I a kisaeng or something?

160
00:11:56,277 --> 00:11:59,407
He wants to invite you to sing at the charity party...

161
00:11:59,507 --> 00:12:01,207
for high officials.

162
00:12:03,707 --> 00:12:07,307
I heard another singer was hired for that event.

163
00:12:08,307 --> 00:12:09,677
She was rushed into a hospital due to acute indigestion.

164
00:12:10,477 --> 00:12:13,277
That's why he wants to invite you.

165
00:12:15,107 --> 00:12:16,477
And he won't take no for an answer.

166
00:12:19,177 --> 00:12:20,277
I don't want to go.

167
00:12:20,807 --> 00:12:22,277
Tell him I was rushed into the hospital as well.

168
00:12:28,277 --> 00:12:30,747
Do you think the high officials will care about your condition?

169
00:12:32,007 --> 00:12:33,407
If you lose their favor,

170
00:12:33,477 --> 00:12:36,207
Carpe Diem will also be marked.

171
00:12:37,007 --> 00:12:39,007
A guest singer? What kind of nonsense is that?

172
00:12:39,647 --> 00:12:42,107
At that time, you have to guard our comrades at Hwanggeumjeong.

173
00:12:42,107 --> 00:12:43,147
You forgot?

174
00:12:43,677 --> 00:12:45,277
But Madam Sophia has a point.

175
00:12:45,807 --> 00:12:49,307
It's a party for high officials. So if I keep refusing to attend,

176
00:12:49,547 --> 00:12:51,877
he might start suspecting me.

177
00:12:51,877 --> 00:12:53,777
You can't go. Refuse it no matter what.

178
00:12:53,877 --> 00:12:56,177
It might affect our whole plan for today.

179
00:12:56,577 --> 00:12:57,577
Besides,

180
00:12:58,547 --> 00:13:00,507
it seems like he's interested in you too.

181
00:13:00,577 --> 00:13:01,647
It doesn't feel right.

182
00:13:03,377 --> 00:13:04,907
I think...

183
00:13:05,277 --> 00:13:06,877
he threw a bait.

184
00:13:07,047 --> 00:13:08,377
It might even be a trap.

185
00:13:08,677 --> 00:13:10,477
Wouldn't it be better for me to go...

186
00:13:10,807 --> 00:13:13,547
than to create suspicion before an important mission?

187
00:13:14,007 --> 00:13:15,777
It makes a good alibi.

188
00:13:15,947 --> 00:13:17,577
If things ever go wrong,

189
00:13:17,577 --> 00:13:19,207
I might be able to help.

190
00:13:19,207 --> 00:13:20,677
Didn't you hear me?

191
00:13:22,547 --> 00:13:24,447
What are you doing, Boss? You should stop her.

192
00:13:25,947 --> 00:13:26,947
Su Hyeon.

193
00:13:30,277 --> 00:13:31,977
Are you confident that you won't be busted?

194
00:13:32,107 --> 00:13:33,147
- Boss. - Of course.

195
00:13:37,447 --> 00:13:39,207
Contact Mr. Nam immediately.

196
00:13:40,007 --> 00:13:43,647
Tell him to fill in for Su Hyeon and guard at Hwanggeumjeong.

197
00:13:44,547 --> 00:13:46,047
- Boss. - Starting right now,

198
00:13:46,947 --> 00:13:48,477
we will change our plan.

199
00:13:49,277 --> 00:13:50,547
Change the plan?

200
00:13:51,177 --> 00:13:53,207
How did I change the plan?

201
00:13:54,007 --> 00:13:56,347
I don't know. That's all I remember.

202
00:13:56,477 --> 00:13:58,007
Is this a TV drama?

203
00:13:58,377 --> 00:13:59,507
Why do you keep cutting it?

204
00:13:59,577 --> 00:14:01,377
Can't I watch the full episode at once?

205
00:14:02,377 --> 00:14:03,647
I think...

206
00:14:04,107 --> 00:14:05,507
it's your turn next.

207
00:14:08,147 --> 00:14:10,007
But I don't remember it at all.

208
00:14:10,877 --> 00:14:13,977
Well, if I were to make use of my brain...

209
00:14:14,477 --> 00:14:17,147
I think Su Hyeon...

210
00:14:17,277 --> 00:14:18,777
brought about the change of the plan.

211
00:14:21,877 --> 00:14:23,207
But what could it be?

212
00:14:25,077 --> 00:14:27,747
Mr. Han, I have something urgent to tell you.

213
00:14:28,577 --> 00:14:30,147
Hide the contract.

214
00:14:31,477 --> 00:14:32,647
Come in.

215
00:14:36,447 --> 00:14:38,407
I didn't know you two were together.

216
00:14:39,047 --> 00:14:40,147
It doesn't matter.

217
00:14:40,277 --> 00:14:41,907
You can go on.

218
00:14:42,707 --> 00:14:45,507
Mr. Son dropped another bomb.

219
00:14:47,547 --> 00:14:49,747
Does he think he is an independent fighter or what?

220
00:14:49,747 --> 00:14:50,877
Why does he keep dropping bombs?

221
00:14:51,647 --> 00:14:53,207
So what is it this time?

222
00:14:53,807 --> 00:14:57,377
I told you. I know nothing about it.

223
00:14:57,377 --> 00:14:58,977
What do you mean it's plagiarized?

224
00:14:59,777 --> 00:15:01,877
That's such a nonsense.

225
00:15:02,207 --> 00:15:04,347
I don't know with what motive...

226
00:15:04,477 --> 00:15:06,977
Mr. Han claimed such accusation,

227
00:15:07,277 --> 00:15:11,547
but that is the work of Mr. Baek.

228
00:15:12,747 --> 00:15:14,807
I have nothing more to say. So I will hang up now.

229
00:15:31,847 --> 00:15:33,307
Han Se Ju.

230
00:15:34,507 --> 00:15:35,877
You scum.

231
00:15:37,807 --> 00:15:38,847
How dare you...

232
00:15:39,777 --> 00:15:41,577
pay us back with grudge?

233
00:15:47,977 --> 00:15:49,007
Well,

234
00:15:49,577 --> 00:15:50,977
why are you speechless?

235
00:15:51,577 --> 00:15:52,877
You said we could trust him.

236
00:15:53,577 --> 00:15:56,347
You said we should trust him because he won't open his mouth.

237
00:15:56,407 --> 00:15:57,677
Is this what I get for trusting him?

238
00:15:58,477 --> 00:16:02,207
You are his father. How could you let this happen?

239
00:16:02,277 --> 00:16:04,777
Who said Se Ju is the source of the rumor?

240
00:16:04,847 --> 00:16:06,107
Who else would it be?

241
00:16:06,307 --> 00:16:07,877
You're still on his side.

242
00:16:08,207 --> 00:16:09,647
How can you remain so indifferent?

243
00:16:09,777 --> 00:16:11,647
Check who wrote that article.

244
00:16:12,007 --> 00:16:14,307
It's Mr. Song, the person you trust wholeheartedly.

245
00:16:14,307 --> 00:16:15,547
I told you!

246
00:16:16,207 --> 00:16:17,577
Se Ju...

247
00:16:17,647 --> 00:16:20,677
I told you we should get rid of Se Ju because he would...

248
00:16:20,677 --> 00:16:23,907
get in the way of Tae Min one day.

249
00:16:24,747 --> 00:16:27,847
Even if Se Ju let it out first,

250
00:16:28,707 --> 00:16:31,277
we have nothing to say.

251
00:16:31,907 --> 00:16:32,947
You should...

252
00:16:33,807 --> 00:16:35,677
persuade Tae Min.

253
00:16:35,977 --> 00:16:38,677
It's going to be tough, but he should confess.

254
00:16:39,577 --> 00:16:41,447
That's the only way he can survive.

255
00:16:41,877 --> 00:16:43,807
Is that the only way you can think of with your smart brain?

256
00:16:44,207 --> 00:16:47,207
You are his father, and the only solution you thought of...

257
00:16:47,277 --> 00:16:49,547
is to bury him alive. Is that it?

258
00:16:49,547 --> 00:16:51,977
It won't bury him. It will revive him.

259
00:16:52,577 --> 00:16:55,207
He should admit his faults and reflect on himself.

260
00:16:55,507 --> 00:16:58,377
Only then he will be able to put everything behind and move forward.

261
00:16:59,977 --> 00:17:02,077
If Tae Min doesn't do it, I will...

262
00:17:02,077 --> 00:17:03,207
If you do that,

263
00:17:04,377 --> 00:17:05,747
I won't...

264
00:17:07,647 --> 00:17:08,947
forgive you.

265
00:17:11,317 --> 00:17:13,407
We're being flooded with requests for fact verification.

266
00:17:14,047 --> 00:17:15,447
How should I respond to this, sir?

267
00:17:16,177 --> 00:17:17,777
Hold off the official statement.

268
00:17:17,777 --> 00:17:19,547
Tell them to wait until we hear from both writers and...

269
00:17:19,547 --> 00:17:21,317
release an official statement.

